<p>My .htaccess looks like this..</p>  <pre><code>Options -Indexes  &lt;IfModule mod_rewrite.c&gt; RewriteEngine On RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f RewriteRule ^(.*)$ index.php [QSA,L]  RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^sub\.domain\.com$ [NC] RewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://www.domain.com/members/invite/$1 [R,L]  &lt;/IfModule&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I want to be able to redirect an URL that looks like this..</p>  <pre><code>https://sub.domain.com/ZTHF76 </code></pre>  <p>to...</p>  <pre><code>https://www.domain.com/members/invite/ZTHF76 </code></pre>  <p>But instead I am getting</p>  <pre><code>https://www.domain.com/members/invite/index.php </code></pre>  <p>I need to keep the first rule to remove <code>index.php</code> from the URI of the rest of the application.</p>  <p>Any help with this greatly appreciated.</p>